article.description:
Don Chaney yanked Howard Eisley and inserted Frank Williams early in the third quarter, a snap coaching decision
that may have saved Chaney's job. The Knicks won 103-92 over the Hawks in New York.
article.headline: Williams sparks 15-0 third-quarter run
article.story:
NEW YORK -- Don Chaney yanked Howard Eisley and inserted Frank Williams early in the third quarter, a snap coaching decision that may have saved Chaney's job. Williams had four assists in a 15-0 third-quarter run that gave New York the lead for good in a 103-92 victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Saturday night. The victory was just the third in 11 games for the Knicks (10-18), whose coach is reportedly in danger of being fired if the team continues to languish amid the lower half of the woeful Atlantic Division. Chaney gave an impassioned defense of himself in a pre-game meeting with reporters, saying he doesn't want or need any reassurances from management that his job is safe. "It's been on the line since I took it," Chaney said of the job he inherited after Jeff Van Gundy resigned unexpectedly more than two years ago. "If I weren't working hard and doing the best I could, then I would be concerned. But I know inside I'm happy with myself because my teams are prepared as well as they can be prepared." Keith Van Horn scored 11 of his 20 points in the fourth quarter, and Allan Houston also had 20 for New York. Williams contributed nine assists, all but two coming in the second half when he played the majority of the minutes at point guard. Chaney turned to Williams just 2:46 into the second half after Eisley had a shot blocked by Jason Terry and then lost the ball out of bounds. A 19-footer by Houston began the 15-0 run that turned a 61-54 deficit into a 69-61 lead. Williams capped the rally with a pair of free throws. The Hawks pulled within six midway through the fourth quarter before Van Horn hit three consecutive 3-pointers for a personal 9-0 run that gave the Knicks a 93-78 lead. Shareef Abdur-Rahim had 20 points to lead the Hawks, who lost their seventh straight overall and their eighth consecutive road game. Game notes
Antonio McDyess had 19 points and 10 rebounds in a season-high 37 minutes. ... Williams scored 10 points. ... Travis Hansen started in place of Dion Glover (flu). ... Houston has made 37 consecutive free throws. ... Atlanta hasn't won at Madison Square Garden since March 22, 1999 -- a span of eight games.
